a comedy of manners twenty plays and the social history of the everyday in 19th century rio de janeiro page 1 2011 2012 clas lecture series presents a comedy of manners twenty plays and the social history of the everyday in 19th century rio de janeiro zephyr frank associate professor of latin american history stanford university this talk will introduce the study of nineteenth century drama as a source for social history it will also explore the way dramatic categories are useful for thinking about society with particular emphasis on staging dialog and character triads the potential utility of computational approaches such as network analysis and topic modeling will be addressed the plays are all comedies so the subject matter should not be inherently boring november 1 2011 12 15 1 05 pm center for latin american studies bolivar house 582 alvarado row light lunch served las stanford edu
